The `toAssocList` converts this list of pairs into an `AssocList`. The `get` operation on an `AssocList` will find the first pair whose key matches the given key and return the corresponding value.

So, `PortMap.getIO` will look up the `Ident` corresponding to `i` (where `i` is `Fin n`) in the `AssocList`. The key in the `AssocList` is `↑i.toNat` (which is just `i` as a natural number). The value is `f i`.

