Then `fin_range n |>.map (λ i => ⟨↑i.toNat, f i⟩)` maps each `Fin n` element `k` to `⟨↑k, f k⟩`.
So the resulting list is `[(↑0, f 0), (↑1, f 1), ..., (↑(n-1), f (n-1))]`.
